  "text": "However, as most of the trading shifts to European markets after around 5:00 pm JST and then to the New York market, in cases where it is considered necessary to intervene during these hours, the Bank of Japan, as the agent of the Minister of Finance, requests foreign monetary authorities to conduct interventions on behalf of the Bank (entrustment intervention).\" [CITATION_1] notes that \"According to the Reuters times-stamp, on average….. the BOJ intervenes at 3:56:36 GMT (or around the Tokyo lunch hour), p. 29\".",
